{NORTH cannot use RKCB at her second bid because trumps have not been agreed. So she bids 
3\H to set trumps, knowing SOUTH cannot pass after her jump-shift. 

SOUTH tries to stop at game but NORTH is too strong so she now uses RKCB and gets 
to 6\H when SOUTH shows two Key Cards and the trump Queen.}

